            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I joined Bridge International School in the fifth grade. Thinking back, it was one of the best decisions of my life. BIS' focus on holistic development not only helped me understand what study methods were the best for me and helped me achieve certain grades, but the numerous activities that were offered also helped me build up my confidence and other soft skills throughout the years.\n\nThis school has also provided me with some of the most unforgettable memories. From looking over the younger ones when the teachers were preparing for Children's Day to us sneaking around them to create charts for Teachers' Day, I had a lovely time outside of my studies. Even during COVID, the teachers went out of their way to keep the classes lively by making us watch videos and telling stories related to the subjects. Not to forget how motivating they were even during the smallest achievements.\n\nLike any other person, there have been ups and downs in my school life, but I will always remain thankful to all of my teachers, non-teaching staff, and fellow students who have been on this journey. You have all helped me become the person I am today, and I will forever miss my school days.",
