            "name": "Bridge International School - Hazra Road"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Pratik Basu"
          },
          "datePublished": "2018-06-16",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "This is probably not the International school that you have in mind. They offer A level & AS level of studies. If you are not sure how A level study works, please do a research before approaching the school as they will put you in confusion. British IGCSE which is equivalent to our class X board exam is taught here, with much lower grades.\nAlso if you apply for Class XI A level (which we did without proper research) , this is not the place to put your ward admitted to. Fees are high compared to the Academic achievements.\nAll their class XII A level achievers are graded in O level standard; basically our class X standard!! You wont get admission in reputed colleges/Universities in that grade.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
